department of management science and engineering academics stanford engineering intranet frequently asked questions bachelor of science does it matter when i declare my major you should declare your major as soon as possible we can then keep you informed of any changes in the program and notify you of events that may be of interest we have no way of contacting undeclared majors can i change my advisor you may change your advisor at any time by contacting ms&e student services how often should i meet with my advisor we recommend that you meet with your advisor on a regular basis and check in with ms&e student services at least once every quarter the first week of each quarter is usually very busy so plan ahead if you need to meet with your advisor or student services during the first week can i transfer credit to stanford students may transfer up to 45 units to stanford all transfer credit must be approved by the registrar's office to use transferred courses to count toward school of engineering requirements math science tis or fundamentals you must submit a petition to the school of engineering student affairs office to use transferred courses to count toward ms&e requirements depth you must submit a petition to the ms&e department student services office can i petition to deviate from the degree requirements students may petition to deviate from school of engineering requirements math science tis or fundamentals by submitting a deviation petition to the school of engineering student affairs office to petition to deviate from ms&e requirements depth submit a deviation petition the ms&e department student services office can i use one course to count for two different degree requirements only gers and the wim requirements may satisfy multiple degree requirements all other courses can be used to satisfy only one degree requirement this includes multiple majors and minors stanford home engineering home ms&e home sitemap contact us 1997 2012 stanford university all righ